                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15 a 1/206: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-28T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1927—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 28—12:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. Your No. 84, April 27, noon. Chamberlain tells me that British Government
                    prefer Geneva for Conference and that they have so notified Japan. They are also
                    taking the necessary steps in regard to League facilities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Houghton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
